{"APPUI":[{"def":"A support or supporter; a stay; a prop.","pos":""}],"APPULSE":[{"def":"The near approach of one heavenly body to another, or to the meridian; a coming into conjunction; as, the appulse of the moon to a star, or of a star to the meridian.","pos":""}],"APPULSION":[{"def":"A driving or striking against; an appulse.","pos":""}],"APPULSIVE":[{"def":"Striking against; impinging; as, the appulsive influence of the planets.","pos":""}],"APPURTENANCE":[{"def":"The structure of the eye, and of its appurtenances.","pos":""}],"APPURTENANT":[{"def":"Annexed or pertaining to some more important thing; accessory; incident; as, a right of way appurtenant to land or buildings.","pos":""}]}